  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Global Citizenship Education in the Asia-Pacific Region through a Whole-School Approach</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims at advancing global citizenship education (GCED) in the Asia-Pacific region by cultivating the awareness of and capacity for a whole-school approach to GCED among teachers and school leaders. It will deliver a Practical Guide on Whole-School Approach to GCED for Teachers and School Leader, as well as provide capacity-building trainings based on the guide for teachers and leaders of pilot schools in the participating countries who will apply the whole-school approach to their work. The pilot-tested Practical Guide will be widely disseminated across and beyond the region.</narrative>
  </description>
